column1: Writ as the Court will not lend itself to making a stultifying order which cannot be
carried out.” The foregoing line of authorities are united in deciding that the delay and
laches are the most significant aspects to be considered in Writ Applications. If there is
a delay and laches on the part of the Petitioner, which has not been explained to the
satisfaction of the Court, the Court will not issue prerogative Writs.”
